Patch Set 5:

Hi Alex Meade, according to you latest response in PS3, I'd like to know whice way you like to go? I tried your property-quota function, and it has the same issue/limitation also, user need to remove his properties first (make property count less than 'image_property_quota' option) before turn down property quota option, otherwise any opertions, even remove a property, will failed by 413 error. TBH this behavior is a little unreasonable and like a defect to end user, do you think we'd better disallow quota checking on property-remove handling in image update action? thanks.

Patch Set 5:

@zhiyan, could you please let me know how did you test the property delete? Because based on my test, against the delete issue, both v1 and v2 work fine.

Patch Set 5:

flwang ask me, I should clarify my thoughts, so:

1. In my latest comments, the "property remove" means set existing perperty's value to None value.
2. So the key to me is that: do you think we'd better allow end user update an existing property to image, even the current property count exceed "image_property_quota" option?

thanks.

Patch Set 5:

I believe with image tags I did address your concern. You should be able to perform a delete on tags even if the result is still over quota.

As for the functionality with image property quotas, I had talked to a few folks including Mark. It is intended that the resulting transaction for image properties must be under the quota. This was decided due to the complex nature of the HTTP PATCH operation and the current domain model implementation. I would love to discuss this further on IRC but this particular patch should not be affected.

Thanks for the quick reviews guys.

Patch Set 5:

I clarify one point for property deletion and like to make sure it whether is an acceptable limitation to us.

If end user already have quota+1 properties, then he can remove one successful since after he remove , the property count value equal quota value, but if end user have quota+N and N>1 property items then remove will be failed since after he remove the property count value still over quota value.

thanks.

Patch Set 5: Looks good to me (core reviewer)

@ameade, thanks for the clarification. Just tested the latest code, the issue I mentioned in PS3 has gone. Thanks for the quick fix. Now this patch looks good for me. But I think we still need more discussion about the same problem against the properties quota patch.
